en


"We've both been so busy lately..."

en

en


"From a purely pragmatic point of view, this is perfect. I need a new successor now that Vina is gone."

en

en


"We have a challenging time ahead of us, that's for certain."

LineNo: 12702302,

en


"A new heir for our holy kingdom. God has truly smiled upon us this day."

She smiled.

A puzzled frown formed on her face.

Tears formed in her eyes. She wrapped her arms around me.

She wrapped her arms around me.

en

en

en

en

en

"This will have huge implications for the future of the monarchy. The sooner we find out, the better."

en

en


My bodyguard entered the room. He cast an eye over myself and Lucita, then reached out to shake my hand.

en

en

en


"Pabel! I'm going to be a father again!"

en

en

en

en


A series of emotions passed across his face as he absorbed this news. Finally, he reached out to shake my hand.

en


"Congratulations to you both. You must be very proud."

en

en

en

en

en

en

en

en


She blushed.

en

"Now that you've done away with the Royal Council, we don't have a reason for secrecy any more."

From behind me, I thought I heard Titus clear his throat.

en

en

In the medical wing, we were received immediately by a group of nurses.

en

en


Her face scrunched up.

Player_Romus: I can't wait to spread the gospel...
en

Narrator: Her face scrunched up.
en


Her face scrunched up.

LineNo: 12713158,

Lucita Azaro: Yes.
en

en


She squeezed my hand.

en

My wife was just over four months along.

en


And we were having a boy.

Narrator: Pabel was standing over my bed with...
en


Pabel was standing over my bed with the morning paper. He had an unusually intense look in his eyes.

en

en

Player_Romus: Can't I sleep in a little longer?
en

en

Pabel pulled back the covers and joined me in bed. He opened the newspaper and gestured at an article.

Pabel Adria: Rufus Gragg is at it again.
en


"Rufus Gragg is at it again."

Pabel Adria: This is my copy of the Herald, tha...
en

en


Pabel sat down at the edge of the bed. He opened the newspaper and gestured at an article.

en


"I was just perusing today's Herald when I saw this."

Player_Romus: What's he writing this time?
en


"What's he writing this time?"

Player_Romus: Remind me. Why haven't I fired him...
en


"Remind me. Why haven't I fired him yet?"

Player_Romus: However bad he is, I'm sure the Vo...
en

LineNo: 12716194,

Narrator: Pabel cleared his throat and adopte...
en


Pabel cleared his throat and adopted an exaggerated Rumburgian accent.

LineNo: 12716574,

Pabel Adria: He's the only gossip columnist in...
en


"He's the only gossip columnist in the country. You can't deny his influence."

Pabel Adria: He doesn't wield as much influence...
en


"He doesn't wield as much influence as he used to now that the press has opened up. But still..."

Pabel Adria: His gossip has been harmless up to...
en


"His gossip has been harmless up to now. A useful distraction."

Pabel Adria: Actually, the Voice has intelligen...
en


"Actually, the Voice has intelligently recognized that there are more urgent things to worry about than the King's love life."

Pabel Adria: 'Who *is* Lord Pabel Adria? From h...

Pabel Adria: Since the Royal Wedding, Lord Adri...
en


"Since the Royal Wedding, Lord Adria has hardly strayed from His Majesty's side. They seem to share that rarest of treasures: a childhood friendship that has stretched well into middle age."

LineNo: 12717742,

Pabel Adria: Though he keeps a low profile, Lor...
en


"Though he keeps a low profile, Lord Adria has been seen by His Majesty's side on numerous occasions. They seem to share that rarest of treasures: a childhood friendship that has stretched well into middle age."

LineNo: 12717844,

Pabel Adria: 'Who *is* Pabel Adria? From humble...
en


"'Who *is* Pabel Adria? From humble beginnings as a groundskeeper's son to head butler to the Royal Family, this man now commands the exclusive attention of the King."

Pabel Adria: His Majesty is hardly ever seen wi...
en


"His Majesty is hardly ever seen without Mr. Adria by his side. Not uncommon for a personal attendant, but these two seem to share that rarest of treasures: a childhood friendship that has stretched well into middle age."

Pabel Adria: Perhaps it is the depth of that sp...
en


"Perhaps it is the depth of that special bond which has kept our King from seeking out a new Queen Consort."

Pabel Adria: Or could it be that he has already...
en

en


"I'm used to such speculations about me. But they should leave you out of this."

Player_Romus: That's as bad as it gets? Ha. It's...
en


"That's as bad as it gets? Ha. It's not like they can arrest us."

LineNo: 12718480,

Player_Romus: If only you could be my Queen Cons...
en


"If only you could be my Queen Consort, Pabel."

LineNo: 12718582,

Pabel Adria: But this...
en


"But this..."

en


"My daughter just died, dammit! Can't a King get any privacy?"

LineNo: 12719056,

Pabel Adria: No, they can't. Thanks to you.
en


"No, they can't. Thanks to you."

LineNo: 12719158,

Narrator: He sighed wistfully.
en


He sighed wistfully.

LineNo: 12719260,

Pabel Adria: I got myself into this when I got...
en


"I got myself into this when I got myself into your trousers."

LineNo: 12719362,

Pabel Adria: Apparently not.
en


"Apparently not."

LineNo: 12719464,

Pabel Adria: What if we could just be out in th...
en


"What if we could just be out in the open about us?"

LineNo: 12719566,

Player_Romus: It's true. I lost my daughter. The...
en


"It's true. I lost my daughter. The worst thing that could ever happen to me has already happened."

LineNo: 12720224,

Pabel Adria: You've already let go of your powe...
en


"You've already let go of your power. What's the worst thing that could happen?"

Pabel Adria: I mean it. What's the worst that c...
en


"I mean it. What's the worst that could happen?"

Player_Romus: I'll be usurped, Laughed off the t...
en


"I'll be usurped, Laughed off the throne."

Player_Romus: You're right. I am the king. My su...
en

Player_Romus: I don't want to jeopardize my daug...
en


"I don't want to jeopardize my daughter's future rule."

LineNo: 12721052,

Player_Romus: The entire world will know that th...
en


"The entire world will know that the King of Rizia enjoys the company of men."

Player_Romus: My daughter ran away. It's been on...
en

en


"Yes. And?"

Pabel Adria: I can't imagine how much pain you'...
en


"I can't imagine how much pain you've been in."

en

en


"A good point. I know how much Her Highness wants to be queen."

en

LineNo: 12721798,

Pabel Adria: Well, precisely. What's one more?
en


"Well, precisely. What's one more?"

LineNo: 12721900,

Pabel Adria: Let's be real. They won't all love...
en


"Let's be real. They won't all love this."

"Let's test the waters first. We'll tell my mother."

"I'm having Rufus Gragg fired. We've got to keep this under wraps."

en


"Why not?"

Pabel Adria: All right.
en


"All right."

"But we can't go on forever like this. Sooner or later, the truth will out."

en


He got up and smoothed out his suit.

He bowed and walked out.

en


He nodded his assent.

She answered, still in her bathrobe.

en

"Pabel and I have something to tell you."
